 ). Antibodies related to autoimmune encephalitis were still negative in the serum and CSF. Therefore, CNS-IRIS was considered. The patient received high-dose intravenous methylprednisolone (20 mg/d/kg body weight, 5 days) followed by oral corticosteroids.
